snippet.textDisplay: I love how this song is extrinsically about a cheating spouse/partner but if you think about it, intrinsically it’s about the ephemeral self cheating the true self. If you think about it even if the spouse cheats with someone else he/she is truly cheating on themselves as it is easy to indulge in a hedonistic lifestyle without any care but the true test is to resist the fake high this indulgence provide. This song to me is a person’s battle against 2 selves but at this point it seems like the indulgent one is winning but the true self is pleading for it to stop indulging further before it’s too late...
